column5: Headed out today to one of my old stomping grounds. Got out late because I slept through my alarm and didn't get on the water till close to noon. However we did have steady action throughout the day.  Baits that worked - Strike king zero, Yum dingers, Gary Y. Senkos, Livetarget frog and Berkley Havoc...  Enjoy the pics.
nice going  that frog looks great
looks like it was a fun day
Nice!!!!  The inches are piling up for Team 4!
Nice fish...but i'm more envious of the I-pilot !
is the black & blood red bait the Berkley Havoc?
Stop posting reports of little fish  nice work bud, i'm so jealous that you get to go out during the week
gawd I'm dying to go frog fishing and this post just kills me! haha
Nice fish...gotta love the top water action!  Are you fishing the senko's wacky rigged or weedless?
thanks guys for the comments!  yes eman, that bait is the berkley havoc but it was missing one or two of the paddles/tails in the pictures.  so vic, sunday? lol  PickerelHunter, I was doing texas rig
